This guide will help you create an authentication form for users to sign in manually.

## Requirements

To follow the steps in this tutorial, you should be familiar with the required directory structure for your code base, and understand the concept of pages and users.

* [Required Directory Structure](/how-platformos-works/platformos-components)
* [Pages](/get-started/pages/pages)
* [Users](/get-started/users/users)

## Steps

Signing in a user manually is a two-step process:

1. Create authentication form
2. Create sign in page

### Step 1: Create authentication form

Create a form `sign_in.liquid` in the `marketplace_builder/form_configurations/` directory:

{% raw %}

<pre><code class="language-liquid">
---
name: sign_in
resource: Session
configuration:
  email:
  password:
---
{% form %}
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;label for="email"&gt;&lt;abbr title="required"&gt;*&lt;/abbr&gt; Email&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;input name="{{ form_builder.fields.email.name }}" value="{{ form_builder.fields.email.value}}" id="email" type="email"&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;label for="password"&gt;&lt;abbr title="required"&gt;*&lt;/abbr&gt; Password&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;input name="{{ form_builder.fields.password.name }}" id="password" type="password"&gt;
      {% if form_builder.errors.password %}
        &lt;p&gt;{{ form_builder.errors.password }}&lt;/p&gt;
      {% endif %}
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  {% submit 'Log In' %}
}
{% endform %}
</code></pre>

{% endraw %}

### Step 2: Create sign in page

Create a page `sign_in.liquid` in the `views/pages` directory to make the sign in available at `/sign-in`:

{% raw %}

<pre><code class="language-liquid">
---
slug: sign-in
---
<h2>Sign in </h2>
{% render_form 'sign_in' %}
<p>New user? Create <a href="/developer/sign-up"> new developer account</a> or <a href="/client/sign-up">new client account</a></p>
</code></pre>

{% endraw %}

